  "prompt": "Is it true ousting of Sucha Singh Chhotepur was done to higher the chances of Kejriwal for becoming CM Punjab?",
  "response": "The ousting of Sucha Singh Chhotepur, a former leader of the Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) in Punjab, has been the subject of political speculation and controversy. Some supporters of Chhotepur and critics of the AAP have suggested that his removal was strategically timed to strengthen Arvind Kejriwal's position and enhance the party's chances in the Punjab elections. They argue that Chhotepur's leadership was seen as a liability for the party.\n\nHowever, the official stance from the AAP leadership has been that the decision was based on allegations of corruption and issues of party discipline. It is essential to note that political maneuvers are often complex and influenced by multiple factors, including public perception, party dynamics, and electoral strategies.\n\nUltimately, whether the decision was indeed made to bolster Kejriwal's chances of becoming Chief Minister depends on different interpretations and the political narratives surrounding the incident. The situation is reflective of the often turbulent nature of party politics in India.",
